<subSubSection pageNumber="736" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="736">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">Note:</emphasis>
Verdcourt (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">Taxon</emphasis>
46: 357. 1997) proposed a conserved type for the name, duly recommended by the Committee for Spermatophyta (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">Taxon</emphasis>
48: 369. 1999), as was the conservation of the spelling 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“helvolus”">&quot;helvolus&quot;</normalizedToken>
. However, Delgado Salinas &amp; Lavin (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">Taxon</emphasis>
53: 839. 2004) subsequently found that the conserved type (U.S.A. North Carolina, Biltmore, sandy flats, 19 Aug 1896; Biltmore herb. No. 1302, US No. 966089) was identifiable as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Muhl. ex Willd.) Britton. They" authorityName="Britton. They" baseAuthorityName="Willd." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Strophostyles" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umbellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">Strophostyles umbellata</emphasis>
(Muhl. ex Willd.) Britton. They
</taxonomicName>
successfully proposed the replacement of 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Verdcourt’s">Verdcourt's</normalizedToken>
type with another conserved type corresponding with current usage of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="736">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Elliott" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Strophostyles" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helvola">S. helvola</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
